  <discussion>Gemmabryum dichotomum is a widespread species exhibiting a temperate bipolar distribution. The Southern Hemisphere material, G. dichotomum in the strict sense, has plants that are larger than Northern Hemisphere material that has traditionally gone under the name of Bryum bicolor but are otherwise similar. Ecologically, plants like those in the Southern Hemisphere are much more common and often dominant in Antarctic to subantarctic tundra vegetation, while typical Northern Hemisphere plants are primarily temperate in distribution.</discussion>
